article.description: Mike Lewis II scored 20 points while Darius Lewis and Josh Steel each scored 13 and Duquesne held off Cleveland State for a 78-71 win on Sunday to conclude the Bluegrass Showcase.
article.headline: Duquesne hold off Cleveland St. rally in 78-71 win
article.linkText: Duquesne hold off Cleveland St. rally in 78-71 win
article.story: PITTSBURGH -- Mike Lewis II scored 20 points while Darius Lewis and Josh Steel each scored 13 and Duquesne held off Cleveland State for a 78-71 win on Sunday to conclude the Bluegrass Showcase. Eric James made a pair of free throws to put Duquesne up 61-43 with 9:40 to go before Cleveland State scored 18 straight to tie it. Kasheem Thomas was 6-for-7 shooting from the free throw line and made a pair of layups during the run. Duquesne (2-4) proceeded to outscore the Vikings 17-10 in the final five minutes to preserve the win. Darius Lewis' layup with 1:26 to go put the Dukes up 76-69. The Dukes led 33-30 at the break. Thomas led Cleveland State (1-4) with 16 points and six assists, Rob Edwards had 15 points and eight boards, and Kenny Carpenter added 13 points for the Dukes. The all-time series is now tied at two games apiece. The teams last met in the 2002-03 season.
